    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, dissolve the <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>redcurrant jelly</strong> and <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> to the softened onion and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>stock</strong> to the pan, increase the heat to medium-high and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened to a ragu-like consistency</p>",
